reviewText: I liked seeing Elvis and Frank  sing together. Some parts might seem silly today but overall it worth watching. Viewers also get to see 1960 Timex comercials.
Not enough Elvis and too much Timex. Should have been much better even for the 60's. Just watch a film with highlight clips from the show: This is Elvis or many others.
I really liked Elvis's performances in this episode. The only problem is that the film is pretty bad, but not so bad you can't see what anyone is doing.

Absolutely amazing to see how bad early television really was.  The only significance of this show is that it was filmed shortly after Elvis demilitarized.  Other than that, it is not too good and the recording itself is terrible.
Good video! Interesting piece of filmed history. Great to see Frank and his daughter working together. Elvis coming back to show business...especial moment!
Realize that this was early TV but horrible picture quality. Would not recommend. Rent early movies or just grab a good CD
The quality of the audio & video are very poor. With today's technology I would have thought it would be better.

This is Elvis at his greatest!  Back from the Army and chomping at the bit to get going again with his singing and acting careers!  He introduced his latest single, "Stuck on You" and flip side, "Fame and Fortune."  So fantastic!  And his duet with Frank Sinatra is historical.  This is a must to have and I'm so delighted with my purchase.  I watch it on my Kindle Fire and it's just a touch away from being highly entertained whenever you need that Elvis fix!
I really enjoyed the Elvis and Frank duets. If technically possible, it would be great if the two estates agreed to blue ray the video.
The quality is not very good, but it's a great show.
This was a great moment in history to watch. Since it is old, the  visual quality is poor but it's a masterpiece none the less.
Even being a "child of the 50s" did not help me appreciate this mess. Corny, extremely poor quality grainy video and scratchy sound. Glad I did not know what I was missing then.
Awesome
Enjoyed seeing these two icons together. A young Nancy Sinatra with her dad.
Good, clean entertainment. Love Elvis.
Only for hard-core buffs of early, grainy black & white television shows. In these days of remastered oldies, this combination of two giants of music leaves a lot to be desired.
poor video quality
Frank and Elvis. It doesn't get better than that.
Sinatra at his best, even when admitting he was wrong about Elvis. He showed true class and respect for the men and woman of the Armed Forces.
Thoughat that Elvis would be singing. After about 15 minutes I shut it off.
Too bad the quality isn't better. We still will watch these old shows no matter what.

totally bad sound and video and the 1950's TV shows were horable. Music chosen was poorly produces and presented with a minimum of background and musical support. TOTAL WASTE OF TIME EVEN FOR FREE PRIME TIME VIEWING
Awesome
In this show, Elvis was an afterthought.
Enjoyed the show!
old timed commerals amazing  rat pack good. frank and elvis  good
Not enough Elvis

It was interesting to see Elvis, though he didn't appear until the end of the show, which was 99% about Frank, with some inane sketch with his two buddies, which wasn't very good. I didn't remember the Frank Sinatra show, and I'm glad I didn't.
Awful singing except for Elvis. The Chairman of the Board should spin in his grave that this is out there of him.
Great fo my Dad who is in a nursing home with dementia. He can't watch anything for more than a few seconds, but he watched this for a full half hour - mesmerized.
It was obvious Frank Sinatra did not like sharing a stage with Elvis

Watching this silvery old print of a Sinatra TV show makes me remember nights in front of the television set. Sitting on the floor, cross-legged, with my brother. It reminds me that the person who HAD to introduce us to Elvis was our babysitter. Then there was old Blue Eyes, just in case you forgot who had the ring-a-ding-ding. Did these guys ever feel like themselves without a scotch on the rocks and a cigarette? Into that mix comes Elvis - country and all youth and testosterone, without SIDEBURNS!

The girls in the audience screamed and shrieked to see him. So would I have, had I not been sitting there in the dark, watching those images on the tv screen. What a trip.
nice show flashbacks
Alway great to see the great Frank Sinatra.
Old video, not the best quality.  Still nice to see...The commercials were fun to see also.
The quality was not great, turned it off shortly after starting.
Watching Elvis snap his fingers on the wrong beats and mangle "Witchcraft" was pretty painful
Perhaps just a sign of earlier times.  I found this very boring.  Elvis had little spotlight, until the end.
